    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix M3AP Session Response IE Value Assignment and Deprecated API Usage\n\n### Summary\nThe M3AP MBMS session response handling in the MCE module had multiple critical issues that caused incorrect message encoding and potential crashes. The `MCE_send_MBMS_SESSION_START_RESPONSE`, `MCE_send_MBMS_SESSION_STOP_RESPONSE`, and `MCE_send_MBMS_SESSION_UPDATE_RESPONSE` functions were not properly setting IE values, using deprecated ASN.1 sequence addition APIs, and had incorrect IE type assignments.\n\nSpecifically, the SESSION_START_RESPONSE function was leaving MCE_MBMS_M3AP_ID and MME_MBMS_M3AP_ID IEs uninitialized, causing the MME to receive malformed responses. Additionally, all three response functions were using the deprecated `asn1cSeqAdd` macro which has known safety issues, and the SESSION_STOP_RESPONSE and SESSION_UPDATE_RESPONSE functions were incorrectly assigning both IEs to the same MCE_MBMS_M3AP_ID value instead of their respective correct values.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure MCE to handle MBMS session requests from MME\n2. Trigger an MBMS session start procedure\n3. Observe that the MME receives a SESSION_START_RESPONSE with uninitialized IE values\n4. When the MME tries to parse these values, it encounters invalid data leading to:\n   - Segmentation faults during ASN.1 decoding\n   - Protocol errors due to missing mandatory IEs\n   - Failed MBMS session establishment\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/COMMON/m3ap_messages_types.h`: Enhanced `m3ap_session_start_resp_t`, `m3ap_session_stop_resp_t`, and `m3ap_mbms_session_update_resp_t` structures to include `mme_mbms_m3ap_id` and `mce_mbms_m3ap_id` fields\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: \n  - Replaced deprecated `asn1cSeqAdd` macro with direct `ASN_SEQUENCE_ADD` calls\n  - Fixed IE value assignments to properly set MCE_MBMS_M3AP_ID and MME_MBMS_M3AP_ID values\n  - Corrected SESSION_STOP_RESPONSE and SESSION_UPDATE_RESPONSE to use proper IE types\n  - Updated function signatures to use correct response structure types\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE_interface_management.h`: Updated function signature for SESSION_STOP_RESPONSE\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_MCE.c`: Fixed message structure references in function calls\n"
}